recordings.loc: Port Elizabeth, Port Elizabeth, Eastern Cape
recordings.rmk:
This South African rarity has been seen at this same spot since January 2016. It relocated about 3km east during our winter and returned to this position again in spring. This was the first time that I have heard it calling.

The recording was done as a video, therefore the only modification was the extraction of the audio from the video. The bird was feeding and preening at low tide in the mud channel just before sunset. It was chased by a Whimbrel shortly after this sound was recorded. The general condition of the bird is good.

Unfortunately conditions were quite windy and there is a lot of traffic noise in the background.
